{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.yaml:snakeyaml:2.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2004-fails-javac-compile-org.yaml-snakeyaml-2.0-0c95d775\n\nThe run started as a `javac` failure caused by SnakeYAML 2.0 API changes: `CustomClassLoaderConstructor(ClassLoader)` no longer matches, and the old `Constructor(TypeDescription)` / `Constructor(String)` usages now expect `LoaderOptions` instead. See `human-intervention-logs/org.yaml:snakeyaml:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T14-50-10-211186Z.log`.\n\nThe most likely blocking stage after the attempted repair was JVM test validation, not native-image compilation. In `human-intervention-logs/org.yaml:snakeyaml:2.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-02T14-53-25-720038Z.log`, repeated `:test` / `:javaTest` runs fail in `ConstructorConstructScalarTest.constructsTaggedBeanWhenContextClassLoaderCannotResolveTheTagClass()` and `CustomClassLoaderConstructorTest.resolvesTaggedBeanWithProvidedClassLoaderWhenContextLoaderRejectsIt()` with `Global tag is not allowed`, even though later native reruns succeeded in `human-intervention-logs/org.yaml:snakeyaml:2.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T14-53-25-736615Z.log` and `.../gradle-test-2026-05-02T14-54-29-078068Z.log`.\n\nThe preserved branch did not retain a fix: `stats/org.yaml/snakeyaml/2.0/execution-metrics.json` reports `status: failure`, `starting_commit == ending_commit` (`a99f50cb8a5d2b01c5580dad3b5e58a8f8611505`), `generated_loc: 0`, and no test or metadata artifact was produced.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Recreate the `tests/src/org.yaml/snakeyaml/2.0` test project from the failing scaffold and update it for SnakeYAML 2.0 constructor/loader APIs.\n2. Fix the two tagged-bean JVM tests so they comply with SnakeYAML 2.0 tag restrictions instead of failing with `Global tag is not